item.description:
Ring out the old, ring in the new, Ring happy bells, across the snow!
The year is going, let him go;
Ring out the false, ring in the true.
TENNYSON
&ldquo;You are old, Father William,&rdquo; the young man said,
&ldquo;And your hair has become very white;
And yet you incessantly stand on your head- Do you think, at your age, it is right?&rdquo;
-LEWIS CARROLL
&ldquo;CONTINUITY HAS broken down,&rdquo; wrote Jules Méline about the changing world around him.
